A verb is a word.
A verb has a present, the shape it takes in an act.
A verb has a past, the shape it takes in a fact.
A verb forms its past from its present with -ed, unless it declares its own.

Declare is a verb.
Call is a verb.
Name is a verb.
Move is a verb.
Grant is a verb.

Make is a verb.
Its past is made.

Give is a verb.
Its past is gave.

Take is a verb.
Its past is took.

See is a verb.
Its past is saw.

Speak is a verb.
Its past is spoke.

Do is a verb.
Its past is did.

Set is a verb.
Its past is set.

Be is a verb.
Its past is was.
Its past is were, for many.

Drop is a verb.
Its past is dropped.
